Reflection 320 Software Test, Automation QA

I ensured my software is functional and secure by developing directly from documented requirements and validating each rule through automated unit tests. In the Contact Service project, 
I implemented strict input validation (length limits, non-null checks, unique IDs) and tested both positive and boundary cases to ensure reliability.

To interpret user needs, I translated written requirements into enforceable system constraints and map each requirement to test cases. This ensures traceability between stakeholder expectations and implemented functionality.

My software design approach is modular and requirement-driven. I separated data models, service logic, and test cases to improve maintainability and scalability. Writing tests alongside implementation allows me to confirm 
correctness early and build dependable, well-structured systems.
